      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Recognizing revenue only when cash is collected is an outdated method and generally not compliant with GAAP under ASC 606, which focuses on when control of goods or services transfers.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Recording a receivable is a consequence of revenue recognition, not the starting point of the process. The five-step model determines *when* to recognize revenue, which may then lead to recording a receivable.",
