      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Prepaid insurance can be an asset, but deferred outflows are broader than just prepaid insurance. They encompass various transactions that benefit future periods.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Bad debt expense is recognized in the period the sale occurs, when it becomes probable the receivable won't be collected. It's an expense, not a deferred outflow.",
