    educational: "Encumbrance accounting is a crucial tool for governmental entities to manage their budgets effectively. By recording encumbrances, governments can track outstanding commitments and prevent overspending, ensuring that funds are available when the actual expenditures occur. This helps maintain fiscal responsibility and transparency.",
