      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - RSUs are valued at the market price of the company's stock on the grant date because the employee will receive shares outright, not the option to purchase them. The expense is then recognized systematically over the vesting period.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - RSUs do not have an exercise price because the employee receives actual shares of stock at vesting, not the option to buy shares.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Par value is an arbitrary value assigned to shares upon issuance and has no bearing on the fair value measurement of RSUs.",
