    explanation: "Under ASC 606-10-55-49, breakage represents the portion of prepaid amounts (gift cards, loyalty points, vouchers) that customers are not expected to exercise. If the entity expects to be entitled to breakage, it recognizes the expected breakage amount in proportion to the pattern of rights exercised by the customer. For example, if 30% of redemptions occur in Year 1, then 30% × $80,000 (8% × $1,000,000) = $24,000 breakage revenue is recognized in Year 1. If breakage CANNOT be reasonably estimated, the entity recognizes revenue only when the likelihood of the customer exercising remaining rights becomes remote.",
