      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Waiting until gift cards expire to recognize breakage revenue is not in accordance with ASC 606. The standard requires recognition based on the pattern of redemption, not a fixed expiration date.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Unredeemed gift cards do not remain a liability indefinitely. ASC 606 provides guidance for recognizing breakage revenue when it's probable that a portion of the gift cards will not be redeemed.",
