      2: "Why option C is WRONG - $84,000 represents 80% of the DTA, but the 80% limitation on NOL usage in future years does not affect the initial calculation of the DTA itself.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Net operating losses create deferred tax assets because they represent a future tax benefit that can be used to reduce taxable income in subsequent years.",
