    correctAnswer: 3,
    explanation: "Under ASC 740-10-30-18, entities evaluate four sources of future taxable income to assess DTA realizability: (1) Future reversals of existing taxable temporary differences — the most reliable because they will definitely reverse. (2) Taxable income in prior carryback years — reliable if available, but TCJA eliminated most carrybacks. (3) Future taxable income exclusive of reversals — requires estimation and judgment, moderately reliable. (4) Tax planning strategies — prudent and feasible actions the entity would take to prevent an NOL or credit from expiring; these are the LEAST reliable because they are hypothetical, may involve costs, and require implementation. A valuation allowance is needed when it is more likely than not the DTA will not be realized.",
