      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Taxable income in prior carryback years is a reliable source of future taxable income if carrybacks are permitted because it is based on actual taxable income from prior periods, although recent tax law changes have limited their availability.",
      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - Tax planning strategies are the LEAST reliable source because they are hypothetical actions the company *could* take, but are not guaranteed. They depend on management's ability and willingness to implement them, and may involve costs or risks.",
