    explanation: "Under ASC 730-10-25-2, research and development costs are generally EXPENSED as incurred under GAAP. This includes costs for designing, testing, and developing a new product or process. However, legal fees, filing fees, and other costs directly associated with OBTAINING the patent (the legal registration) ARE capitalized as the cost of the patent intangible asset. The capitalized legal costs are then amortized over the shorter of the patent's legal life (20 years) or its useful economic life. If the patent is unsuccessfully defended in litigation, the remaining unamortized cost is written off.",
