      2: "Why option C is WRONG - R&D costs are not deferred under GAAP; they are expensed immediately. Deferral implies future benefit, which is not reliably measurable for general R&D activities.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - The timing of successful patent acquisition doesn't dictate the treatment of R&D costs. R&D costs are expensed regardless of whether the patent is ultimately granted; only the direct costs of obtaining the patent are capitalized upon successful acquisition.",
