      1: "Why option B is WRONG - Interest cost reflects the increase in the PBO due to the passage of time and is calculated by multiplying the beginning-of-year PBO by the discount rate.",
      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - Plan amendments create prior service cost, which is initially recorded in Other Comprehensive Income (OCI) and then amortized to pension expense over the remaining service life of the employees. It is not immediately recognized in net income.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - The expected return on plan assets reduces pension expense. It reflects the anticipated earnings from the pension plan's investments.",
