      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The lender does not take ownership of the receivables in an assignment; they only have a security interest in them. The receivables remain the property of the assignor.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Writing off receivables as a loss is only appropriate when they are deemed uncollectible, not when they are assigned as collateral.",
