    difficulty: "easy",
    skillLevel: "Remembering and Understanding",
    question: "Under ASC 320, debt securities classified as trading are reported on the balance sheet at:",
    options: ["Amortized cost","Fair value, with unrealized gains and losses in net income","Fair value, with unrealized gains and losses in OCI","Lower of cost or market"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 320-10-35-1, trading debt securities are measured at fair value, with unrealized gains and losses recognized in NET INCOME. Trading securities are acquired with the intent to sell in the near term (active and frequent buying/selling). This treatment results in the most volatile income statement impact among the three categories. In contrast: HTM securities are at amortized cost, and AFS securities are at fair value with unrealized gains/losses in OCI. The classification is based on management's intent and ability at the time of acquisition. Reclassification between categories is permitted but rare and subject to specific guidance.",
