    difficulty: "hard",
    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "A company sells a product to a customer for $100,000 with a forward agreement to repurchase the product for $110,000 in 12 months (the repurchase price exceeds the selling price). Under ASC 606, this arrangement is accounted for as:",
    options: ["A sale with a right of return","A financing arrangement — no revenue is recognized, and the $10,000 difference is recognized as interest expense over 12 months","A consignment arrangement","Revenue of $100,000 with a separate repurchase liability of $110,000"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 606-10-55-70, when an entity has an obligation or right to repurchase the asset (a forward or call option), and the repurchase price is greater than the original selling price, the transaction is accounted for as a FINANCING arrangement (not a sale). The entity: (1) Does NOT derecognize the asset. (2) Recognizes a financial liability of $100,000. (3) Recognizes the difference ($110,000 − $100,000 = $10,000) as interest expense (or cost of financing) over the 12-month period. The customer does not obtain control of the asset because the entity's obligation to repurchase indicates the company has not transferred control.",
