    examTip: "Remember the direction of the sale: 'Upstream' means the subsidiary sold to the parent, affecting NCI; 'Downstream' means the parent sold to the subsidiary, not affecting NCI.",
    memoryAid: "Upstream = NCI affected (think 'Up' the chain of command, affecting everyone).",
    reference: "ASC 810-10-45-1",
