    question: "A company discontinues a cash flow hedge because the forecasted transaction is no longer probable of occurring. Under ASC 815, the amounts in accumulated OCI related to this hedge are:",
    options: ["Left in AOCI until the transaction occurs","Reclassified into net income immediately","Reversed against the hedging instrument","Transferred to retained earnings"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 815-30-40-4, when a cash flow hedge is discontinued because it is PROBABLE that the forecasted transaction will NOT occur within the originally specified time period, the net gain/loss that was accumulated in OCI is reclassified into earnings IMMEDIATELY. If the hedge is discontinued but the forecasted transaction is still probable, the amounts in AOCI remain until the forecasted transaction affects earnings. If the hedging instrument is sold/terminated but the forecasted transaction is still probable, AOCI amounts remain and are reclassified when the transaction occurs. The key distinction is whether the transaction is still probable.",
