    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 815-25-35, in a fair value hedge: (1) The gain/loss on the hedging instrument ($48,000 gain) is recognized in net income. (2) The change in fair value of the hedged item attributable to the hedged risk ($50,000 loss) is also recognized in net income (with a corresponding adjustment to the carrying amount of the inventory). The net effect — $2,000 — represents hedge INEFFECTIVENESS, which is always recognized in net income in a fair value hedge. The carrying amount of the inventory is reduced by $50,000 (which will affect COGS when sold). Under ASU 2017-12, the presentation of hedging gains/losses may be in the same income statement line item.",
