    explanation: "Under ASC 815-10-15-83, a derivative has THREE defining characteristics: (1) It has one or more underlyings (interest rate, price, exchange rate, etc.) and one or more notional amounts or payment provisions. (2) It requires no initial net investment or a small initial investment relative to direct exposure. (3) Its terms require or permit NET SETTLEMENT (cash settlement, delivery of an easily convertible asset, or market mechanism for settlement). Being traded on an organized exchange is NOT a requirement — over-the-counter (OTC) derivatives like interest rate swaps and forward contracts also qualify. However, certain contracts are excluded from derivative treatment (e.g., regular-way purchases/sales, insurance contracts, certain financial guarantee contracts).",
