    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 205-40-50-12, even when substantial doubt is alleviated by management's plans, disclosure is still REQUIRED. The disclosures include: (1) Principal conditions or events that raised substantial doubt (before considering management's plans). (2) Management's evaluation of the significance of those conditions. (3) Management's plans that alleviated the substantial doubt. This \"intermediate\" disclosure level (doubt raised but alleviated) is less extensive than when doubt is NOT alleviated. If doubt is NOT alleviated, additional disclosures are required, including a statement that there is substantial doubt about continuing as a going concern. The financial statements are NOT presented on a liquidation basis if the entity continues as a going concern.",
