    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 810-10-40-5, when a parent loses control of a subsidiary, it deconsolidates the subsidiary and: (1) Derecognizes the subsidiary's assets and liabilities. (2) Derecognizes any NCI. (3) Recognizes the fair value of the consideration received. (4) Remeasures ANY RETAINED noncontrolling investment (the 40%) to FAIR VALUE at the deconsolidation date. (5) Recognizes a gain or loss calculated as: FV of consideration received + FV of retained interest − carrying amount of the former subsidiary's net assets (including goodwill) − carrying amount of NCI. The retained 40% interest is then accounted for under the equity method (if significant influence exists) or as an equity investment going forward.",
