      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - ASC 805 mandates that the consideration transferred in a business combination be measured at fair value at the acquisition date. This includes all forms of consideration given by the acquirer, such as cash, assets, liabilities assumed, and equity interests issued, all measured at their fair values.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Historical cost is a backward-looking measure and does not reflect the current economic value of the consideration transferred at the acquisition date. Fair value provides a more relevant and reliable measure for business combinations.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - The acquiree's book value of net assets is irrelevant to the measurement of the consideration transferred by the acquirer. The acquirer's consideration is measured at its fair value, independent of the acquiree's book values.",
