    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 815-20-25-3, hedge accounting requires FORMAL DOCUMENTATION at inception of the hedging relationship. The documentation must include: (1) The hedging RELATIONSHIP (the entity's risk management objective and strategy). (2) The hedging INSTRUMENT (including the specific derivative). (3) The hedged ITEM or transaction (the specific asset, liability, firm commitment, or forecasted transaction). (4) The nature of the risk being hedged. (5) How the entity will assess hedge EFFECTIVENESS (including the method and frequency). (6) For cash flow hedges of forecasted transactions: the probability and timing. ASU 2017-12 allows a \"reasonable period\" after designation to complete documentation but retains the inception requirement for designation.",
