      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - ASC 250 requires that a voluntary change in accounting principle be justified by demonstrating that the new principle is preferable because it results in more reliable and relevant financial reporting. This ensures that changes are made to improve financial reporting, not to manipulate results.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While industry practices can be a factor in determining preferability, simply stating that competitors use the new method is insufficient justification. The entity must still demonstrate that the new method provides more reliable and relevant financial reporting.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Reducing tax liability is not an acceptable reason for changing accounting principles under GAAP. Financial reporting should reflect the economic reality of the business, not solely minimize tax obligations.",
