      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Consolidated retained earnings reflect the accumulated profits of the consolidated group attributable to the parent company's shareholders; intercompany dividends don't impact the overall profitability of the group.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While dividends paid *to* noncontrolling interests are a financing activity, dividends paid *from* a subsidiary to its parent are eliminated and do not appear on the consolidated cash flow statement because they are internal transfers.",
