      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The conventional retail method approximates the lower of cost or market, not inventory at cost. Including markdowns in the calculation would get you closer to inventory at cost.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Excluding markdowns *directly* affects the cost-to-retail ratio, making it lower than it would be if markdowns were included.",
