    educational: "The conventional retail method aims to approximate the lower of cost or market value without tracking the actual cost of each item. By excluding markdowns from the cost-to-retail ratio, the method implicitly recognizes that the market value of some goods may have declined below their original cost, leading to a more conservative inventory valuation.",
    examTip: "Remember that the conventional retail method is designed to approximate the lower of cost or market, so excluding markdowns creates a more conservative valuation.",
