      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Recognizing revenue ratably over 3 years is appropriate for services performed over time, not for a single sale of equipment where control transfers immediately. The revenue recognition should occur at the point of sale, adjusted for the financing component.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Deferring all revenue until payment is received contradicts the core principle of ASC 606, which emphasizes recognizing revenue when control of the goods or services transfers to the customer. Control transfers at the time of sale, even with delayed payment.",
