    explanation: "Under ASC 350-30-35-18, indefinite-lived intangible assets (such as certain trademarks, broadcast licenses, or perpetual franchise rights) are not amortized. Instead, they are tested for impairment at least annually, or more frequently if events or changes in circumstances indicate it is more likely than not that the asset is impaired. The impairment test compares the fair value of the intangible to its carrying amount — any excess of carrying amount over fair value is recognized as an impairment loss. The entity must reassess indefinite-life classification each period.",
