    explanation: "ASC 740-10-25-6 uses a two-step process: Step 1 (Recognition): Determine whether it is more likely than not (>50% likelihood) that the tax position will be sustained upon examination, based solely on technical merits. If not, no benefit is recognized. Step 2 (Measurement): If the threshold is met, measure the benefit as the largest amount of benefit that is greater than 50% likely of being realized upon settlement. The analysis assumes the taxing authority has full knowledge of all relevant information. Interest and penalties on uncertain positions are recognized under ASC 740-10-45-25.",
