    explanation: "Under ASC 740-20-45-2, intraperiod tax allocation allocates total income tax expense for the period among: (1) continuing operations, (2) discontinued operations, (3) other comprehensive income, and (4) items charged or credited directly to equity (such as prior period adjustments, stock compensation effects, or changes in accounting principles). Cost of goods sold is not a separate allocation category for income tax. The total income tax remains the same — it is simply allocated to the appropriate components of comprehensive income and equity.",
