      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Other comprehensive income (OCI) items, such as unrealized gains/losses on certain investments, can have tax effects that are allocated to OCI through intraperiod tax allocation.",
      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - Cost of goods sold (COGS) is an operating expense that affects income from continuing operations; its tax impact is already included within the tax expense allocated to continuing operations, not separately allocated.",
