      1: "This option calculates the total fair value difference of the building ($150,000) and amortizes it over 10 years ($15,000), but it fails to consider the investor's 40% ownership stake, making it an incorrect calculation of the investor's share of the amortization.",
      2: "This option represents the investor's share of the *total* fair value difference of the building ($150,000 * 40% = $60,000) but incorrectly assumes this amount is the annual amortization. Amortization requires dividing the depreciable amount by the asset's useful life.",
      3: "Amortization *is* required when the fair value of an identifiable asset differs from its book value at the time of investment and the equity method is used. The difference must be amortized over the asset's remaining useful life, affecting the investor's share of the investee's income.",
