    educational: "ASC 420 addresses accounting for exit or disposal cost obligations, including one-time termination benefits. The standard aims to ensure that companies recognize these liabilities when they have a present obligation to employees due to a communicated plan, rather than delaying recognition until the actual termination occurs. This provides a more accurate representation of the company's financial position.",
    examTip: "Focus on the trigger event for liability recognition: the communication of a detailed termination plan to employees, not just management's internal approval or the actual termination.",
