    explanation: "Under ASC 842-10-25-8, a lease modification that grants an additional right of use not in the original lease is treated as a separate contract if: (1) the modification increases the scope by adding the right to use one or more underlying assets, AND (2) the consideration is commensurate with the standalone price for the additional right of use adjusted for the contract circumstances. If both criteria are met, it's a separate lease. If not, the lessee remeasures the lease liability using a revised discount rate and adjusts the ROU asset accordingly.",
