    explanation: "Under ASC 820-10-35-10, the fair value of a nonfinancial asset is based on its highest and best use as determined by market participants. Highest and best use considers what is physically possible, legally permissible, and financially feasible. The current use is presumed to be highest and best use unless market evidence suggests otherwise. For financial assets and liabilities, highest and best use is not relevant since they are fungible. This concept is particularly important for real estate and specialized assets.",
