      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The lease liability is based on the present value of future lease payments. Lease incentives received at or before commencement do not affect the amount owed in the future and therefore do not increase the lease liability.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Lease incentives are not expensed immediately. Instead, they reduce the ROU asset, which is then amortized over the lease term, impacting lease expense over time.",
