    explanation: "ASC 280-10-50-1 uses a management approach to segment identification. Operating segments are components of an entity: (1) that engage in business activities from which revenues and expenses are incurred, (2) whose operating results are regularly reviewed by the CODM for resource allocation and performance assessment, and (3) for which discrete financial information is available. The CODM is a function, not a title — it may be the CEO, COO, or a group of executives. This approach aligns external reporting with how management actually views and manages the business.",
