    educational: "ASC 280, Segment Reporting, aims to provide financial statement users with a view of the company through the eyes of management. This 'management approach' ensures that external reporting reflects how the company is actually run, allowing investors to better understand the drivers of performance and make informed decisions. The CODM's reports are the key to unlocking this internal perspective.",
    examTip: "When a question mentions segment reporting, immediately think of the 'management approach' and the CODM's reports; this will help you quickly eliminate incorrect options.",
