      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Pension expense is an income statement item, reflecting the cost of the pension plan for the current period, not the overall funded status on the balance sheet.",
      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - ASC 715 mandates recognizing the funded status (difference between plan assets and PBO) on the balance sheet. Unrecognized gains/losses and prior service costs are reported in Accumulated Other Comprehensive Income (AOCI).",
