    educational: "Defined benefit pension plans create a long-term obligation for the company. The balance sheet reflects whether the company has sufficient assets to cover this obligation (asset) or if it's underfunded (liability). Any differences between the accounting expense and the actual funding are adjusted through AOCI.",
    examTip: "Remember that the balance sheet reflects the *status* of the pension plan (funded or underfunded), while the income statement reflects the *expense* for the period.",
    memoryAid: "Balance Sheet = Status; Income Statement = Expense",
