      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The cost method is generally used for investments where the investor has little to no influence. Upon deconsolidation, the retained investment is initially measured at fair value, not cost.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Discontinued operations reporting is for components of an entity that have been disposed of or are classified as held for sale. While the loss of control might lead to a disposal, it's the deconsolidation and gain/loss recognition that are the immediate accounting treatments.",
