    educational: "Fair value hedging aims to protect a company from changes in the fair value of an asset or liability. By using a hedging instrument, the company seeks to offset any losses (or gains) on the hedged item with gains (or losses) on the hedging instrument, thereby stabilizing earnings.",
    examTip: "Remember that fair value hedges are all about offsetting changes in fair value in current earnings, so look for answer choices that reflect this simultaneous recognition.",
