    options: ["The host contract is a financial instrument","The combined instrument is not measured at fair value with changes in earnings, the embedded derivative meets the definition of a derivative, and the economic characteristics of the embedded derivative are not clearly and closely related to the host","The embedded derivative has a notional amount exceeding $1 million","The host contract is with a foreign counterparty"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 815-15-25-1, an embedded derivative must be bifurcated from the host contract and accounted for at fair value as a derivative if ALL three conditions are met: (1) the combined instrument is not remeasured at fair value with changes recognized in earnings; (2) the embedded component, if freestanding, would meet the definition of a derivative under ASC 815-10-15-83; and (3) the economic characteristics and risks of the embedded derivative are not clearly and closely related to those of the host contract. Common examples include conversion features in debt, put/call features in debt at other than par, and equity-indexed interest rates.",
