    options: ["Only the mark-to-market approach","Either the mark-to-market approach (recorded in earnings immediately) or a systematic and rational amortization approach (amortized over the life of the hedging instrument)","Only amortization over the hedged item's useful life","Through AOCI without ever recycling to earnings"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASU 2017-12 (codified in ASC 815-20-25-83A) allows entities to exclude certain components of the hedging instrument (e.g., time value of options, forward points on forwards, cross-currency basis spreads) from the assessment of hedge effectiveness. The excluded components can be recognized using either: (1) a mark-to-market approach — changes in fair value of the excluded component are recognized in current earnings each period; or (2) an amortization approach — the initial value of the excluded component is amortized on a systematic and rational basis over the life of the hedging instrument, with the difference between the change in fair value and the amortization amount recorded in OCI.",
