      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - ASC 718 mandates that share-based compensation, such as stock options and restricted stock, be measured at its fair value on the grant date. This fair value is then expensed over the service period, reflecting the cost to the company of providing this compensation.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Par value is an arbitrary value assigned to shares upon issuance and has no relevance to the fair value measurement required for share-based compensation under ASC 718.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Book value reflects the historical cost of assets less accumulated depreciation and is unrelated to the fair value measurement of share-based compensation at the grant date.",
