    educational: "Discontinued operations reporting is reserved for significant disposals that fundamentally alter the company's business. The updated standard aims to reduce the number of disposals classified as discontinued operations, focusing only on those representing a strategic shift with a major impact. This provides investors with a clearer picture of the company's ongoing operations.",
    examTip: "Remember the key phrase 'strategic shift with a major effect' when identifying discontinued operations on the exam.",
    memoryAid: "Think 'SMS' - Strategic shift, Major effect, Stop (discontinued).",
