      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Representations about arm's-length terms are permissible under ASC 850, but only if they can be substantiated with evidence.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While the SEC may review financial statements, it does not automatically audit related party transactions solely based on an arm's-length claim; the company's independent auditor is primarily responsible.",
