    educational: "Related party transactions require careful scrutiny because they are not always conducted at market rates. Companies must provide evidence to support any claim that a related party transaction was conducted on terms equivalent to those with an unrelated party. This ensures transparency and prevents misleading financial statement users.",
    examTip: "On the exam, remember that related party transactions are inherently suspect, so any claim of 'arm's length' requires solid proof.",
    memoryAid: "ARM'S LENGTH = ASK FOR RECORDS, MUST SUBSTANTIATE",
    reference: "ASC 850-10-50-5",
