    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASC 205-30-25-1 through 2 requires the liquidation basis of accounting when liquidation is imminent. Liquidation is imminent when: (1) a plan for liquidation has been approved by the entity's governing body and the likelihood that the entity will return from liquidation is remote; or (2) a plan for liquidation is being imposed by other forces (e.g., involuntary bankruptcy) and the likelihood of the entity returning from liquidation is remote. Under the liquidation basis: assets are measured at estimated amounts expected to be collected in liquidation, liabilities include estimated costs of liquidation, and the statement of net assets in liquidation and statement of changes in net assets in liquidation replace traditional financial statements.",
