    options: ["$1,200,000 because the bonus is probable","$1,140,000 (base + 70% of the bonus)","$1,200,000 under the most likely amount method because earning the bonus is the most likely outcome","$1,000,000 because the bonus is contingent and cannot be estimated"],
    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "Under ASC 606-10-32-8, variable consideration is estimated using either the expected value method (probability-weighted) or the most likely amount method. The most likely amount method is appropriate when the outcome is binary (bonus earned or not). Since there is a 70% probability of earning the bonus, the most likely outcome is receiving the full $200,000 bonus. Therefore, the transaction price is $1,200,000 under the most likely amount method, subject to the constraint that it is probable a significant revenue reversal will not occur.",
