    explanation: "Under ASC 842-10-25-2, a lease is classified as a finance lease if any ONE of five criteria is met: (1) Transfer of ownership at end of lease, (2) Purchase option reasonably certain to be exercised, (3) Lease term is a major part (≥75%) of remaining economic life, (4) PV of lease payments equals substantially all (≥90%) of fair value, or (5) Asset is specialized with no alternative use to lessor. If none of these criteria are met, it is an operating lease. Both finance and operating leases result in right-of-use assets and lease liabilities on the balance sheet.",
