      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The ARO increases the carrying value of the related asset, which directly impacts the depreciation expense recognized each year.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - The obligation exists now, even though the settlement is in the future. AROs are recognized when a reasonable estimate of the fair value can be made, regardless of the settlement date.",
