      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Held-to-maturity (HTM) securities are measured at amortized cost, not fair value, so unrealized gains and losses are not applicable. They are only reported at amortized cost as the company intends to hold them until maturity.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Not all debt securities have unrealized gains and losses reported in OCI; only AFS securities do. Trading securities go to net income, and HTM securities are held at amortized cost.",
