    question: "On January 1, Year 1, a company grants 10,000 stock options with a grant-date fair value of $8 per option. The options vest over 3 years (cliff vesting) and the company estimates 5% forfeitures. What compensation expense is recognized in Year 1?",
    options: ["$80,000","$26,667","$25,333","$24,000"],
    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "Under ASC 718, compensation cost for stock options is measured at the grant-date fair value and recognized over the requisite service period. Total compensation cost = 10,000 options × $8 × (1 - 5% estimated forfeitures) = 10,000 × $8 × 0.95 = $76,000. With 3-year cliff vesting and straight-line recognition: Year 1 expense = $76,000 ÷ 3 = $25,333. Under ASU 2016-09, entities may elect to recognize forfeitures as they occur instead of estimating them, but if estimates are used, they must be updated each period with a cumulative catch-up adjustment.",
