    educational: "Stock option compensation expense is recognized over the service period, which is the time employees must work to earn the options. The expense is based on the grant-date fair value of the options, adjusted for estimated forfeitures. This total compensation cost is then allocated over the vesting period, typically using a straight-line method.",
    examTip: "Always remember to account for estimated forfeitures and the vesting period when calculating stock option compensation expense.",
    memoryAid: "GVF: Grant-date Value, Forfeitures, Vesting period - remember these three to calculate stock option expense.",
