    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 340-40-25-1, incremental costs of obtaining a contract are capitalized if the entity expects to recover those costs. Incremental costs are those that would not have been incurred if the contract had not been obtained (e.g., sales commissions). The capitalized asset is amortized on a systematic basis consistent with the pattern of transfer of goods or services. A practical expedient allows immediate expensing if the amortization period would be one year or less. Costs to fulfill a contract are capitalized under ASC 340-40-25-5 if they relate directly to the contract, generate or enhance resources, and are expected to be recovered.",
