      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Incremental costs of obtaining a contract are not treated as a reduction to revenue. They are considered an asset representing future economic benefit.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Incremental costs of obtaining a contract are not directly related to the production of goods or services, so they are not included in cost of goods sold. They are a separate asset representing the cost of acquiring the contract.",
