    explanation: "Under ASC 360-10-35-17, the impairment process for long-lived assets held for use is a two-step process: Step 1 (Recoverability test): Compare the carrying amount to the sum of undiscounted expected future net cash flows from the asset's use and eventual disposition. If carrying amount ≤ undiscounted cash flows, no impairment exists. Step 2 (Measurement): If carrying amount > undiscounted cash flows, the impairment loss equals carrying amount minus fair value. Note: this differs from goodwill impairment (ASC 350), which uses fair value directly without the recoverability screen.",
