    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under the treasury stock method (ASC 260-10-45-22): (1) Assume all options are exercised: 100,000 shares issued, proceeds = 100,000 × $20 = $2,000,000. (2) Assume proceeds are used to repurchase shares at the average market price: $2,000,000 ÷ $25 = 80,000 shares repurchased. (3) Incremental (dilutive) shares = 100,000 issued - 80,000 repurchased = 20,000 shares. Options are dilutive only when the exercise price is below the average market price (in-the-money). These 20,000 shares are added to the denominator in diluted EPS.",
