    examTip: "Remember to always check if the options are 'in-the-money' (exercise price < average market price) before applying the treasury stock method; otherwise, they are anti-dilutive and ignored.",
    memoryAid: "Treasury Stock Method: 'Proceeds Repurchase Incremental' - Proceeds from exercise are used to Repurchase shares, and the difference is the Incremental dilutive shares.",
    reference: "ASC 260-10-45-22",
