      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The lease incentive reduces the ROU asset, which is amortized. It is not treated as a deferred credit related to the useful life of the leasehold improvements themselves.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Reducing lease expense only in the first year would misrepresent the economic substance of the lease, as the benefit of the incentive extends over the entire lease term.",
