    educational: "Lease incentives are designed to encourage a lessee to enter into a lease agreement. Under ASC 842, these incentives are treated as a reduction in the lessee's cost of obtaining the right to use the underlying asset, reflecting the net economic benefit to the lessee. This approach ensures that the financial statements accurately portray the economics of the lease transaction over its entire term.",
    examTip: "Remember that lease incentives always reduce the ROU asset; think of it as a discount on the asset's initial value.",
    memoryAid: "ROU REDUCTION: Reimbursements Offered Understate Right-of-use.",
