    options: ["$15,000 loss in net income","$6,000 credit loss in net income (through allowance) and $9,000 in OCI","$15,000 in OCI with no income statement impact","$6,000 in OCI and $9,000 in net income"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 326-30 (CECL for AFS debt securities), when an AFS security is impaired: (1) If the entity intends to sell or will be required to sell, the entire decline ($15,000) is recognized in net income. (2) If NOT intending to sell, the credit-related loss ($6,000) is recognized in net income through an allowance for credit losses (not a direct write-down), and the noncredit portion ($9,000) is recognized in OCI. This bifurcation preserves the ability to reverse the credit loss through the allowance if credit conditions improve, unlike the previous OTTI model which required direct write-downs.",
