    options: ["$500,000","$396,916 (present value of the note)","$443,458","$103,084"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 835-30, when a note is exchanged for property and the stated rate of interest is not reasonable (or there is no stated rate, as in a zero-interest note), the note is recorded at its present value. The difference between the face amount ($500,000) and the present value ($396,916) is discount of $103,084, which represents interest. The equipment is recorded at $396,916 (the fair value of the note). Over the 3-year term, the $103,084 discount is amortized as interest expense using the effective interest method. The note's carrying amount increases from $396,916 to $500,000 at maturity.",
