      2: "Why option C is WRONG - $443,458 is not a relevant calculation in this scenario. The equipment's cost is determined by the present value of the note, not an arbitrary amount between the present value and face value.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - $103,084 represents the discount on the note (the difference between the face value and the present value), which will be amortized as interest expense over the life of the note. It is not the initial value of the equipment.",
