    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "A quasi-reorganization (ASC 852-20) allows a company with a large accumulated deficit to get a \"fresh start\" without going through formal bankruptcy proceedings. The process involves: (1) Restating assets and liabilities to fair values (usually writing them down, which may increase the deficit). (2) Eliminating the accumulated deficit by offsetting it against additional paid-in capital (APIC). (3) If APIC is insufficient, the par or stated value of stock may be reduced. After the quasi-reorganization, retained earnings starts at zero, and the entity must disclose the date of the quasi-reorganization for 10 years.",
