      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While issuing new stock could theoretically improve the balance sheet, it's not the defined mechanism for eliminating a deficit in a quasi-reorganization, which focuses on internal restructuring of equity accounts.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Accumulated Other Comprehensive Income (AOCI) is a separate component of equity used for specific items like unrealized gains/losses on certain investments, not for absorbing a retained earnings deficit in a quasi-reorganization.",
