    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "A lessee occupies 3 floors under a 10-year operating lease. In Year 4, the lease is modified to surrender 1 floor (one-third of the leased space), reducing future payments proportionally. The ROU asset is $900,000 and lease liability is $960,000 before modification. How is the partial termination accounted for?",
    options: ["Reduce both by one-third and recognize any difference as a gain or loss","Reduce the lease liability by the proportional decrease in payments and adjust the ROU asset; recognize any difference as gain or loss","No adjustment — continue with the original amounts","Immediately expense the entire remaining ROU asset"],
