    educational: "When a lease is partially terminated, it's treated as a significant change to the original agreement. Accounting standards require a proportional adjustment to both the Right-of-Use (ROU) asset and the lease liability to reflect the reduced scope of the lease. Any difference resulting from these adjustments is recognized as a gain or loss in the period of the modification.",
    examTip: "On the exam, carefully identify if a lease modification is a full or partial termination, as the accounting treatment differs significantly.",
