    options: ["No additional cost — the original fair value continues","Incremental cost = $4,000 ($4 × 1,000); the unrecognized portion of original cost plus incremental cost is recognized over the remaining service period","$14,000 total cost starting from the modification date","Incremental cost of $4,000 recognized immediately"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 718-20-35-3, when an award is modified (Type I — probable-to-probable vesting), the entity recognizes: (1) The original cost continues — the remaining unrecognized cost from the original award. At 60% complete: original total = $10 × 1,000 = $10,000; recognized so far = $6,000; remaining = $4,000. (2) Incremental cost = (new FV − old FV) × number of options = ($14 − $10) × 1,000 = $4,000. This incremental cost is recognized over the remaining service period. (3) Total remaining cost = $4,000 (orig. remaining) + $4,000 (incremental) = $8,000 over remaining 40% of the service period.",
