    explanation: "To determine income tax expense: Start with pre-tax book income ($1,000,000). Permanent differences: Tax-exempt interest ($50,000) reduces taxable income permanently, nondeductible fines ($30,000) increase taxable income permanently. Taxable income approximation: $1,000,000 − $50,000 + $30,000 = $980,000. However, income tax expense per GAAP has two components: (1) Current tax expense based on taxable income, and (2) Deferred tax expense for temporary differences. With no temporary differences stated, total tax expense = $980,000 × 21% = $205,800. Wait — permanent differences affect both book and taxable income the same way. Actually: Tax expense = ($1,000,000 − $50,000 + $30,000) × 21% = $205,800. Effective rate = 20.58%.",
