    explanation: "Under ASC 470-50-40-10 (the \"10% test\"), a debt restructuring between an existing borrower and lender is treated as an extinguishment (not a modification) if the present value of cash flows under the new terms differs by MORE than 10% from the present value of remaining cash flows under the old terms, discounted at the ORIGINAL effective interest rate. If it is an extinguishment: derecognize old debt, record new debt at fair value, recognize gain/loss. If it is a modification (≤10% difference): adjust the effective interest rate prospectively, no gain/loss. Third-party fees are also treated differently depending on the classification.",
