      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The lender's agreement is necessary for the restructuring to occur, but it doesn't automatically classify the restructuring as an extinguishment. The 10% test determines the accounting treatment.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Whether or not the loan balance changes is not relevant to determining if the restructuring is an extinguishment or a modification. The present value of cash flows is the key factor.",
