    educational: "When a debt is restructured, it's crucial to determine if it's a simple modification or a more significant extinguishment. The 10% test, based on the present value of cash flows, helps make this distinction. Remember to discount the *old* debt's cash flows at the *original* interest rate when performing this calculation.",
    examTip: "On the exam, carefully identify the original interest rate and use it to discount the old debt's cash flows when applying the 10% test.",
    memoryAid: "10% Test: New PV vs. Old PV (discounted at the ORIGINAL rate). Over 10%? Extinguishment!",
