      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Acceptance by the consignee simply means they've received the goods for holding; it doesn't signify a transfer of ownership or revenue recognition for the consignor.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Revenue is not recognized ratably over the consignment period because the actual sale (transfer of control) hasn't occurred yet; revenue recognition is tied to the specific event of sale to the end customer.",
