    question: "A lessor enters a direct financing lease for equipment with a cost of $500,000 and fair value of $500,000. Annual rental payments are $80,000 for 8 years, with no residual value. The implicit rate is approximately 5.84%. At commencement, how does the lessor record the lease?",
    options: ["Debit Lease Receivable $640,000 (total payments), Credit Equipment $500,000, Credit Unearned Income $140,000","Debit Net Investment in Lease $500,000, Credit Equipment $500,000","Debit Accounts Receivable $80,000, Credit Lease Revenue $80,000","No entry — direct financing leases are off-balance sheet for lessors"],
