    options: ["$800,000","$400,000","$300,000","$100,000"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Goodwill at acquisition = $5,000,000 − $4,200,000 = $800,000. Under ASC 350-20-35 (simplified impairment test), impairment loss = Carrying amount of reporting unit − Fair value of reporting unit = $5,300,000 − $4,900,000 = $400,000. The loss is capped at the carrying amount of goodwill ($800,000), so the full $400,000 is recognized. This eliminates the old Step 2 implied fair value calculation.",
