    options: ["$150,000","$60,000","$120,000","$48,000"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Intercompany profit on the upstream sale = $500,000 − $350,000 = $150,000 total markup. Since 40% of the goods remain in the buyer's ending inventory, unrealized profit = 40% × $150,000 = $60,000. This $60,000 must be eliminated in consolidation (reducing ending inventory and increasing COGS). In an upstream sale, the elimination is allocated: 80% to the controlling interest and 20% to the noncontrolling interest.",
