    examTip: "Always focus on the portion of goods *remaining* in the buyer's inventory when calculating unrealized intercompany profit; the percentage sold is irrelevant for this calculation.",
    memoryAid: "UP - Unrealized Profit = Unsold Percentage * Profit",
    reference: "ASC 810-10-45",
