    examTip: "When determining fund balance classifications, always consider the source and strength of the constraint; the more binding and permanent the constraint, the higher the classification in the hierarchy.",
    memoryAid: "Think of 'NARCU' - Nonspendable, Assigned, Restricted, Committed, Unassigned - as a reminder of the fund balance hierarchy from most to least restricted.",
