    educational: "Conditional promises are recognized as revenue only when the conditions are substantially met or explicitly waived by the donor. This is because until the conditions are met, the organization does not have an unconditional right to the assets and the donor retains the right of return or release from the obligation. Unconditional promises, on the other hand, are recognized immediately.",
    examTip: "Focus on the word 'conditional' - it means 'if,' and revenue recognition is deferred until the 'if' happens.",
    memoryAid: "Conditional = Conditions Met = Contribution Revenue",
    reference: "ASC 958-605",
