      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - The loss on factoring is the difference between the carrying value of the receivables ($500,000 - $8,000 = $492,000) and the proceeds received from the factor ($500,000 - $15,000 fee - $25,000 reserve = $460,000 + $25,000 reserve = $485,000). The loss is $492,000 - $485,000 = $7,000.",
