    educational: "Pension accounting aims to reflect the economic reality of providing retirement benefits. Actuarial gains and losses are initially recognized in OCI because they are considered temporary fluctuations that, if immediately recognized in net income, could distort a company's earnings. Amortizing them over time provides a smoother representation of pension expense.",
    examTip: "Remember that actuarial gains and losses are the primary component of net periodic pension cost that bypasses the income statement initially and goes directly to OCI.",
