    educational: "Deferred tax assets represent future tax benefits. A valuation allowance is a contra-asset account used to reduce the carrying value of a deferred tax asset when it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax asset will not be realized. This ensures that assets are not overstated on the balance sheet.",
    examTip: "Remember the phrase \"more likely than not\" when dealing with valuation allowances for deferred tax assets; this is the trigger for recognizing the allowance.",
    memoryAid: "Think of \"More Likely than Not\" as \"MLN\" - and MLN means \"Must Lower Now\" (the DTA with a valuation allowance).",
