    educational: "Diluted EPS reflects the potential dilution of earnings per share if stock options or other dilutive securities were exercised or converted into common stock. The treasury stock method assumes that proceeds from the exercise of options are used to repurchase shares at the average market price. This reduces the dilutive effect by decreasing the net increase in shares outstanding.",
