      0: "Why option A is WRONG - An anonymous contribution simply means the donor's identity is unknown; it doesn't relate to the contribution being conditional.",
      1: "Why option B is WRONG - A restriction to a future time period is a type of donor restriction, but it doesn't create a conditional contribution. The organization still has control of the funds.",
      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - A conditional contribution hinges on the occurrence of a future event that includes both a measurable barrier to overcome and a stipulation that the asset will be returned to the donor if the condition is not met. This uncertainty prevents immediate revenue recognition.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - A donor-specified purpose creates a restriction on the use of the contribution, but it doesn't make the contribution conditional. The organization can use the funds, but only for the specified purpose.",
