    options: ["$1,000,000 — the full grant amount when received","$600,000 — proportional to hours completed","$0 — no revenue until all 5,000 hours are completed","$500,000 — one-half of the grant for partial completion"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 958-605 (as amended by ASU 2018-08), conditional contributions are recognized when conditions are substantially met. A barrier exists (providing 5,000 hours of service). Since 3,000 of 5,000 hours (60%) have been completed, the condition is partially met, and $600,000 (60% × $1,000,000) should be recognized as revenue. The remaining $400,000 is reported as a refundable advance (liability) until the remaining hours are provided.",
