    explanation: "The revenue recognized in 2026 is calculated as follows:\n\n1.  Calculate total revenue as of 2026: $5,000,000 (original contract price) + $800,000 (change order) = $5,800,000\n2.  Calculate the percentage of completion as of 2026: Costs incurred to date ($1,200,000 + $1,500,000 + $1,800,000 = $4,500,000) / Total estimated costs ($4,500,000) = 102.27%. Because the project is 100% complete in 2026, the company will recognize the remaining revenue.\n3. Calculate revenue recognized through 2025: 2024 Revenue = (($1,200,000/$3,600,000)*$5,000,000) = $1,666,667. 2025 Revenue = ((($1,200,000 + $1,500,000)/$4,000,000)*$5,000,000) - $1,666,667 = $1,708,333.\n4. Remaining revenue to recognize in 2026: $5,800,000 - $1,666,667 - $1,708,333 = $2,425,000. However, because the revenue recognized cannot exceed the total contract price, the 2026 revenue is $2,425,000. Rounding to the nearest $100,000 the answer is $2,400,000. \n\nRevenue is recognized based on the percentage of completion. The change order is treated as part of the contract as it is approved by the customer and is likely enforceable. (ASC 606-10-32-14)",
